Market Analysis and Size

The growing use of the cogeneration technique within the expanding venture to increase generation capacity will encourage business expansion. When considering ongoing technological advancements, rising power costs, favorable administrative circumstances, and declining resource costs are the most significant factors that will increase the heat recovery steam generator exchange extension. The International Energy Agency (IEA) projects a 3% CAGR for the power generation sector, where heat recovery steam generators are widely used, over the next few years. This is anticipated to increase demand for gobal heat recovery steam generators (HRSG) in the upcoming years.

